description: This file implements part of a STUN (Session Traversal Utilities for NAT) client, specifically the functions related to processing incoming packets, query handling, and socket event notification within the 'Stun Simple Client Object'. It defines functions that determine how to process incoming STUN messages, handle processing of specific message types (BindingResponse and BindingErrorResponse), and handle socket events.

methods.name: ULONG StunScoScuowoAQuery(ANSC_HANDLE hThisObject,PVOID buffer,ULONG ulSize)
methods.description: Determines how to process an incoming packet based on the object state; returns processing mode.

methods.name: ANSC_STATUS StunScoScuowoAProcess(ANSC_HANDLE hThisObject,PVOID buffer,ULONG ulSize)
methods.description: Processes an incoming STUN message; dispatches to specific handlers based on message type.

methods.name: ANSC_STATUS StunScoScuowoANotify(ANSC_HANDLE hThisObject,ULONG ulEvent,ANSC_HANDLE hReserved)
methods.description: Handles socket-related events, currently implemented as a stub that returns success.
